This paper deals with non-monotonic reasoning, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on logic programming, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of Prolog, which is a programming language commonly used in the field of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The integration of XSB and SMODELS also involves software engineering techniques such as modularity, which could place this paper under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the exploration of knowledge bases and the use of a full Prolog system could also relate to the field of Databases (cs.DB).
